SUMMARY:Rice World Cup Cities Hack
DTSTAMP:20260618T044224Z
DTSTART:20260623T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Rice World Cup Cities Hack is a sustainability-focused virt
	ual data hackathon tied to the FIFA World Cup 2026. Teams will work with r
	eal-world urban datasets to build data management and visualization soluti
	ons\, analyzing the sustainability impact of the World Cup on host cities 
	like Houston. \n📅 Kick-Off Workshop: June 23-24 at The Ion\, Houston – Reg
	ister – https://forms.gle/uBfedtqia27Zmafe7\n💻 Virtual Hackathon: June 23-
	September 15\n🏆 $10\,000 Grand Prize | $17\,500 in total prizes \nChalleng
	e tracks include Transportation & Access\, Energy-Food-Water Nexus\, Publi
	c Health & the Built Environment\, and High-Intensity Corridors & Future G
	rowth Districts. Interdisciplinary teams are encouraged! \n\n\nRegister fo
	r Hack by June 22: https://rice-urban-sustainability.devpost.com/\n\nhttps
	://iondistrict.com/event/rice-world-cup-cities-hack/\n\nFrom Ion District
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/rice-world-cup-cities-hack/
LOCATION:Ion\, 4201 Main Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ion-district
CATEGORIES:Ion District
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT48H
